pkg_lib v1.0.0 | Mar 06 2026:

-- New Features --
  [New] Cron management: pkg_cron_install (auto-detect mode 644/755 from
      destination path), pkg_cron_remove (multi-file removal),
      pkg_cron_cleanup_legacy (glob-based legacy cron cleanup)
  [New] Cron schedule preservation: pkg_cron_preserve_schedule (capture 5-field
      schedule from existing cron file), pkg_cron_restore_schedule (restore
      captured schedule after install overwrite with sed * escaping)
  [New] Documentation installation: pkg_man_install (copy + optional sed
      pairs + gzip + install to auto-detected man dir), pkg_bash_completion
      (install to /etc/bash_completion.d/), pkg_logrotate_install (install to
      /etc/logrotate.d/), pkg_doc_install (README/CHANGELOG/LICENSE to doc dir)
  [New] Internal helper: _pkg_man_dir (resolve man directory with standard/
      FreeBSD/fallback paths per section)
  [New] Config migration: pkg_config_merge (AWK two-pass merge preserving old
      values into new template with comment/ordering preservation),
      pkg_config_migrate_var (rename variable with optional upper/lower
      transform and migration comment), pkg_config_clamp (clamp numeric
      config value to maximum with warning)
  [New] Config primitives: pkg_config_get (AWK single-pass value extraction
      with quote stripping), pkg_config_set (sed-based in-place update or
      append for new variables)
  [New] Cron management tests (07-cron.bats)
  [New] Documentation installation tests (08-docs.bats)
  [New] Config migration tests (09-config.bats)
  [New] Service lifecycle: unified service management primitives normalizing
      systemd/SysV/Gentoo/Slackware init system handling across OS families
  [New] Service install/uninstall: pkg_service_install (unit/init script copy
      with auto-detection), pkg_service_uninstall (exhaustive removal from all
      locations), pkg_service_install_timer, pkg_service_install_multi,
      pkg_service_uninstall_multi for multi-unit service bundles
  [New] Service control: pkg_service_start, pkg_service_stop,
      pkg_service_restart via shared _pkg_service_ctl cascade (systemd → SysV)
  [New] Service configuration: pkg_service_enable with OS-family cascade
      (systemd → chkconfig → update-rc.d → rc-update → Slackware S-links),
      pkg_service_disable (reversible), pkg_service_exists, pkg_service_is_enabled
  [New] rc.local management: pkg_rclocal_add (idempotent, creates file if
      missing), pkg_rclocal_remove (grep -v + atomic replace across all paths)
  [New] Internal helpers: _pkg_systemd_unit_dir (env override + auto-detect),
      _pkg_init_script_path (dual-dir lookup), _pkg_service_ctl (shared cascade)
  [New] FreeBSD early-return guards on all service functions (rc.conf out of
      scope for v1.0.0)
  [New] Service lifecycle tests (06-service.bats, 88 tests)
  [New] Backup & restore: pkg_backup with copy/move methods, DDMMYYYY-EPOCH
      timestamps, collision-safe -N suffixes, configurable .bk.last symlink
  [New] Backup helpers: pkg_backup_exists, pkg_backup_path for symlink queries;
      pkg_backup_prune for age-based cleanup with .bk.last protection
  [New] Restore primitives: pkg_restore_files for selective glob-based restore;
      pkg_restore_dir for full subdirectory restore
  [New] File operations: pkg_copy_tree (recursive copy with attribute preservation),
      pkg_set_perms (dirs/files/executables), pkg_create_dirs (mkdir -p + chmod)
  [New] Symlink management: pkg_symlink (create/update), pkg_symlink_cleanup
      (safe removal, skips non-symlinks)
  [New] Path operations: pkg_sed_replace (sed -i with | delimiter across files),
      pkg_tmpfile (mktemp wrapper with PKG_TMPDIR support)
  [New] Backup/restore tests (04-backup.bats, 34 tests)
  [New] File operations tests (05-fileops.bats, 38 tests)
  [New] Output functions: pkg_header, pkg_info, pkg_warn, pkg_error, pkg_success,
      pkg_section, pkg_item with terminal color detection (_pkg_color_init)
  [New] OS/platform detection: pkg_detect_os with /etc/os-release and legacy
      fallback chain (redhat-release, debian_version, gentoo, slackware, uname)
  [New] Init system detection: pkg_detect_init with systemd, SysV, upstart,
      rc.local cascade; pkg_is_systemd convenience function
  [New] Package manager detection: pkg_detect_pkgmgr with command -v cascade
      (dnf, yum, apt, emerge, pkg, slackpkg); pkg_os_family accessor
  [New] Dependency checking: pkg_check_dep with required/recommended/optional
      levels; pkg_check_deps for batch parallel-array checking; pkg_dep_hint
      for package-manager-specific install hints
  [New] Output function tests (01-output.bats, 21 tests)
  [New] OS detection tests (02-os-detect.bats, 17 tests)
  [New] Dependency checking tests (03-deps.bats, 23 tests)
  [New] Repository skeleton with batsman test infrastructure (v1.0.3)
  [New] Minimal pkg_lib.sh stub with source guard and version variable
  [New] 9-OS Docker test matrix (debian12, centos6-rocky10, ubuntu 12.04-24.04)
  [New] CI workflow with lint + batsman reusable test workflow
  [New] Scaffold validation tests (00-scaffold.bats, 2 tests)
